HOW TO IMPROVE GUT HEALTH?
Follow
1) CONSUME LESS SUGAR
A diet high in sugar has been shown to have a negative effect on the gut microbiome.
2) AVOID UNNECESSARILY ANTIBIOTICS
One of the most important risk factors is the overuse of antibiotics
3) GET ENOUGH SLEEP
Sleep deprivation can lead to a decrease in good bacteria
4) DRINK ENOUGH FLUIDS
Drinking plenty of fluids is a must to avoid constipation
5) REDUCE STRESS
Stress has been shown to cause gut dysbiosis, leaky gut, and inflammation
6 EAT PROBIOTICS
Probiotics help improve gut health by increasing nutrient absorption, improving digestion speeds, and reducing inflammation
7) AVOID ALCOHOL CONSUMPTION
Drinking alcohol is never beneficial to gut health.
8) CONSUME HOMEMADE FOOD
Instead of consuming pre-packaged food, opt to make your own at home.
